A Spring Boot web application built on Docker for monthly work schedules using Thyme Leaf.

The application allows users to register and then, after authentication, use the registered user's individual context.

After authentication, users can select the month for which they would like to plan their work schedule in a spreadsheet-like format displayed in a web browser window.

For each month, they can add additional employees and assign them daily work hours or various forms of absence, such as caregiving, vacation, etc.

Individual work schedules edited in the web browser window are saved and accessible only to the user who saved them.

Ex. end-point

.../form/date-picker/choose-date
# ex. http://localhost:8080/form/date-picker/choose-date
